    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "When trying to run `coverage` against the code in https://github.com/godlygeek/cython-issue-4999, coverage spits out an error:\r\n```\r\nCouldn't parse '/tmp/cython-issue-4999/src/hello_world/_impl.pyx' as Python source: 'invalid syntax' at line 2\r\n```\r\nbecause the `Cython.Coverage` plugin doesn't report that it can handle the `_impl.pyx` file, because it can't resolve its path (it goes looking for it in `cython-issue-4999/hello_world` instead of `cython-issue-4999/src/hello_world`).\r\n\r\nTo reproduce:\r\n```shell-session\r\n$ cd /tmp\r\n$ git clone https://github.com/godlygeek/cython-issue-4999\r\nCloning into 'cython-issue-4999'...\r\nremote: Enumerating objects: 11, done.\r\nremote: Counting objects: 100% (11/11), done.\r\nremote: Compressing objects: 100% (8/8), done.\r\nremote: Total 11 (delta 0), reused 11 (delta 0), pack-reused 0\r\nReceiving objects: 100% (11/11), done.\r\n$ cd cython-issue-4999\r\n$ python3.10 -m venv venv\r\n$ venv/bin/pip install . cython coverage\r\n...\r\nSuccessfully installed coverage-6.4.4 cython-0.29.32 hello-world-0.0.1\r\n$ venv/bin/coverage run test.py\r\nHello, Cython!\r\n$ venv/bin/coverage report\r\nCouldn't parse '/tmp/cython-issue-4999/src/hello_world/_impl.pyx' as Python source: 'invalid syntax' at line 2\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2022-09-24T07:11:24Z",
    "comment_data": [
